Make a project directory then run the following commands

yarn init -y
yarn add apollo-server-express express @apollo/client
npm install graphql
yarn add graphql
npm install react
yarn add react

Create two files in the project directory with name index.js and server.js and copy the code.

Once you have ecexuted the commands above, run the following in the two separate terminals. Make sure you are in the right directory of the project

node server.js

node index.js

Open a web browser and visit http://localhost:4000/graphql. You should see the GraphQL Playground, indicating that the server is running successfully.

Put the following in the query in the playground

query {
posts {
id
title
content
}
}
